# Accessing  Linux Server Remotely Using SSH - Putty | Windows CMD | Gitbash | MobaXtream

1. Make sure you have setup network as on bridged.

2. Open putty and fill centos ip and click Open. now insert username password. SUCCESS CONNECTED.
3. Same as REDHAT LINUX.
4. But in Ubuntu you need to install openssh-server and start the service.

